<?xml-stylesheet href="makehtml.xsl" type="text/xsl"?><section id="v106568322" revision="09222015235924" vendor="referenced"><title id="v106568324">Checking device status<token>RD_about_DS_widget</token>
         </title><para id="v110168658">The <guilabel moreinfo="none">Device Status</guilabel> widget lets you identify the devices that pose a security threat, so that you can take the necessary actions to mitigate the risks. </para><para id="v110318517">You can drill down to get more information about the devices in a particular state. For example, from the drill-down window, you can navigate to the <guilabel moreinfo="none">Groups, Users and Devices</guilabel> page to see all the compromised devices, sorted by operating system and version. When you review the list, you determine that an issue is specific to a particular version of Windows. In this case, you can use the <guilabel moreinfo="none">OS Distribution</guilabel> widget to see all devices that use that version of Windows and take the appropriate action to prevent an outbreak from spreading. 
         </para><itemizedlist id="v106568358"><title id="v106568359">Possible device states are as follows: </title><listitem id="v106568360"><para id="v110999351">Pending
               </para><para id="v111331932">Indicates that device enrollment and security scans are in progress.</para></listitem><listitem id="v110999352"><para id="v106568361">Secure</para><para id="v111331933">Indicates that the device complies with all security requirements.</para></listitem><listitem id="v106568378"><para id="v106568379">At Risk</para><para id="v111331934">Indicates issues on the device that require your attention. For example, virus definitions are outdated.</para></listitem><listitem id="v106568392"><para id="v106568393">Compromised</para><para id="v111331935">Indicates that the device is infected and requires immediate resolution.
                  
